        "title: \"V17 Analysis: Generalized Horizon + Trajectory Probing + Curriculum SIGReg\"\n",
        "date: \"2026-04-18\"\n",
        "format:\n",
        "  html:\n",
        "    code-fold: true\n",
        "    self-contained: true\n",
        "    toc: true\n",
        "    toc-depth: 3\n",
        "    theme: cosmo\n",
        "    fig-width: 10\n",
        "    fig-height: 6\n",
        "execute:\n",
        "  echo: true\n",
        "  warning: false\n",
        "  error: false\n",
        "jupyter: python3\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "## Overview\n",
        "\n",
        "V17 introduces three changes to the V2 (V11) architecture:\n",
        "\n",
        "1. **Fixed-window target + LogUniform horizon**\n",
        "   Old: `target = ema_encoder(x_{t+1:t+k})`, length varies with `k`.\n",
        "   New: `target = ema_encoder(x_{t+k:t+k+w})`, fixed `w=10`, offset `k ~ LogU[1, 150]`.\n",
        "   *Why:* the target's quality is constant across `k`; prediction difficulty alone scales with horizon. Equal-weight training across orders of magnitude of `k`.\n",
        "\n",
        "2. **Trajectory probing**\n",
        "   The predictor `gamma(k) = predictor(h_past, k)` is a latent dynamics model.\n",
        "   Use it at inference: probe on `[h, gamma(5), gamma(10), gamma(20), gamma(50), gamma(100)]` (1536-dim) instead of `h_past` alone.\n",
        "\n",
        "3. **Curriculum EMA -> SIGReg**\n",
        "   Epochs 0-100:   EMA only (proven V2 basin).\n",
        "   Epochs 100-150: EMA + SIGReg `lambda` ramps `0 -> 0.05`.\n",
        "   Epochs 150-200: No target network; target = `stop_grad(encoder(x_{future}))` + SIGReg maintains isotropy.\n",
        "\n",
        "All phases evaluated with **F1 at k=30** (\"fails within 30 cycles?\") alongside RMSE for direct comparison with anomaly detection literature.\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
